ental terrain, this innovative work makes a profound contribution to the study of spectatorship.Key featuresExamines documentaries and essay films, imageless films and art-house cinema, feature-length works and shortsProvides an innovative approach to spectatorship studies by deriving the principal mental processes of image formation that it outlines from the wide selection of films under discussionHighlights how and where imagination and perception relate to one another, thereby opening up the more exclusive foregrounding of perception within recent phenomenological film theory  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFilm criticism. 0aImagination in motion pictures. 0aImagination. 0aMotion pictures. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107804200 cprintz978147445278640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474452809?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474452809423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474452809/original  a978-3-11-078042-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK